title: For Trade:  WTT: Taurus 24/7 Duo-tone (,45 ACP), S&W SW9F, and Norinco/Hawk 982 (870 clone)
postcontent:
WTT: Taurus 24/7 Duo-tone (,45 ACP), S&W SW9F, and Norinco/Hawk 982 (870 clone)

I’ve a couple of guns that really don’t get much use anymore and I’m trying to consolidate my calibers/magazines. 

1. Taurus 24/7 Duo-tone in  .45 acp with 2 magazines (12 rounds each) – I bought this gun new almost 2 years ago on a whim, it looked sexy and a .45.. Ive probably put less than 200 rounds through it; it has a little holster wear mostly in the form on a few light scratchers. The first hundred or so rounds fired flawlessly, the second 100 were giving me some problems with the extractor (common with Taurus) but it looks like it’s been resolved with a thorough cleaning of the extractor and not using Blazer aluminum cased ammo.

2. S&W SW9F in 9mm with 2 magazines (one 17 round and one 10 round) – I picked this one up a while ago because it was a 9mm to save some money on ammo (I’ve always been a 40 cal glock guy), but it doesn’t shoot like anything else I have, even though this is the model that Glock sued S&W over some years ago. It’s got a bit if a heavy trigger pull, but other than that, it’s a great gun. Simple and functional. 

3. Norinco/Hawk 982 – This a Chinese clone of the Remington 870 and will accept 870 parts, other than the barrel and I believe the forend may be welded on, not sure if that can be changed out. I have too many shotguns as it is and this guy gets the least use. 5+1 rounds with ghost ring sights. It has a little wear, but functions perfectly. 

Trades – I’m really only interested in trades at this time, partial +/- cash on either end of the trade depending on how many guns and what they are, you know the deal. 

Email is the best way to get in contact with me, I work in an office and I’m in and out of meetings most of the day. 

-mike

title: For Sale:  M48 Mauser
postcontent:
The M48 Mauser is a post World War II Yugoslavian version of the Belgian Fabrique Nationale designed Mauser Model 1924 short rifle which was produced under contract by the "Kingdom of Yugoslavia" beginning in 1928 and ending with the Nazi occupation in 1941. After World War II, the Yugoslavs took this design and incorporated modifications based upon Germany's Mauser Karabiner 98k. Although similar in general appearance to that of the German rifle, many of the parts of these two rifles are not interchangeable, especially the bolt and related action parts. The main difference between the M48 and the K98k is that the M48 uses an intermediate-length receiver. They are usually easily identified by the top handguard, which extends behind the rear sight and ends just in front of the receiver ring, although this feature exists on other models as well. 

This rifle is in great shape and I can shoot 1-2 inch groups at 100 yards. This price is only good for the weekend. Email me with a cell phone number that I can send pictures to. Thanks

title: For Sale/Trade:  Tagged as: Taurus  45 ACP  Double / Single Action  Pistol
postcontent:
Tagged as: Taurus  45 ACP  Double / Single Action  Pistol  
WTT: Taurus 24/7 Duo-tone (,45 ACP), S&W SW9F, and Norinco/Hawk 982 (870 clone)

I’ve a couple of guns that really don’t get much use anymore and I’m trying to consolidate my calibers/magazines. 

1. Taurus 24/7 Duo-tone in .45 acp with 2 magazines (12 rounds each) – I bought this gun new almost 2 years ago on a whim, it looked sexy and a .45.. Ive probably put less than 200 rounds through it; it has a little holster wear mostly in the form on a few light scratchers. The first hundred or so rounds fired flawlessly, the second 100 were giving me some problems with the extractor (common with Taurus) but it looks like it’s been resolved with a thorough cleaning of the extractor and not using Blazer aluminum cased ammo.

2. S&W SW9F in 9mm with 2 magazines (one 17 round and one 10 round) – I picked this one up a while ago because it was a 9mm to save some money on ammo (I’ve always been a 40 cal glock guy), but it doesn’t shoot like anything else I have, even though this is the model that Glock sued S&W over some years ago. It’s got a bit if a heavy trigger pull, but other than that, it’s a great gun. Simple and functional. 

3. Norinco/Hawk 982 – This a Chinese clone of the Remington 870 and will accept 870 parts, other than the barrel and I believe the forend may be welded on, not sure if that can be changed out. I have too many shotguns as it is and this guy gets the least use. 5+1 rounds with ghost ring sights. It has a little wear, but functions perfectly. 

Email is the best way to get in contact with me, I work in an office and I’m in and out of meetings most of the day. 

-mike

I'd rather trade, but will entertain cash offers.

Will trade for: Things I’d trade for: -Entry level 1911 (RIA or something along those lines) -Kel-Tec Sub2000 in 40 S&W Glock configuration -Berretta Strom Cx4 in any caliber -Some sort of tacti-cool .22lr  -Other pistol caliber carbines
